north of [[Penglai, Shandong|Penglai]]. They are known for their sandy beaches and picturesque limestone cliffs.<ref>[http://grahambond.blogspot.com/2005_09_01_archive.html Bond, Graham (10 September 2005) \"Military Secrets\" ''A'Wandering: News, Opinion and Reports from the Road'']</ref> The total land area is only {{convert|56|sqkm|sp=us|sigfig=2}}, but the coastline is {{convert|146|km|abbr=on|sigfig=2}} long.\n\n==Geography==\nThe '''Changshan Islands''' ({{zh|s=[[:zh:\u957f\u5c71\u5217\u5c9b|\u957f\u5c71\u5217\u5c9b]]|t={{linktext|\u9577\u5c71|\u5217\u5cf6}}|p=Ch\u00e1ngsh\u0101n li\u00e8d\u01ceo}}), also known as the '''Temple Islands''' or '''Miaodao Archipelago''' ({{zh|labels=no |t={{linktext|\u5edf\u5cf6|\u7fa4\u5cf6}} |s={{linktext|\u5e99\u5c9b|\u7fa4\u5c9b}} |p=Mi\u00e0od\u01ceo q\u00fand\u01ceo}}) are an [[archipelago]] of 32 islands located across the southern portion of the [[Bohai Strait]], the [[waterway]] connecting the [[Bohai Sea]] to the [[Yellow Sea]], collectively named after the two largest islands.  In Chinese, they are also known as the \"Long Islands\" ({{zh|labels=no|t={{linktext|\u9577\u5cf6}}|s={{linktext|\u957f\u5c9b}}|p=Ch\u00e1ngd\u01ceo}}), and anciently as the \"Sandy Gate Islands\" ({{zh|labels=no|t={{linktext|\u6c99\u9580|\u5cf6}}|s={{linktext|\u6c99\u95e8|\u5c9b}}|p=Sh\u0101m\u00e9n d\u01ceo}}).\n\n===Administrative Divisions===\nThe Changdao County has jurisdiction over one [[subdistricts of China|subdistrict]], one [[towns of China|town]] and six [[townships of China|township]]s:<ref>http://www.xzqh.org/html/list/2340.html Date=December 13, 2017</ref>\n* Nanchangshan Subdistrict \u5357\u957f\u5c71\u8857\u9053 South Chang Mountain Subdistrict\n* Tuojizhen Town \u7823\u77f6\u9547\n* Beichangshan Township \u5317\u957f\u5c71\u4e61 North Chang Mountain Township\n* Heishan Township \u9ed1\u5c71\u4e61 (Black Mountain Township)\n* Daqindao Township \u5927\u94a6\u5c9b\u4e61 (Big Qin Island Township)\n* Xiaoqindao Township \u5c0f\u94a6\u5c9b\u4e61 (Little Qin Island Township)\n* Nanhuangcheng Township \u5357\u968d\u57ce\u4e61 (South Huang City Township)\n* Beihuangcheng Township \u5317\u968d\u57ce\u4e61 (North Huang City Township)\n===Islands===\nThere are 32 islands in Changshan Islands, and 10 of them have permanent residences.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Name !! Chinese Name !! Length (km) !! Width (km) !! Area (km2) !! Shoreline (km) !! Maximum elevation (m)\n|-\n|South Changshan Island ||\u5357\u957f\u5c71\u5c9b||7.22||4||12.8||20.02||156.1\n|-\n|North Changshan Islands ||\u5317\u957f\u5c71\u5c9b||5.1||2.6||7.87||13.8||195.7\n|-\n|Greater Heishan Island ||\u5927\u9ed1\u5c71\u5c9b||4.22||2.7||7.47||12.03||189\n|-\n|Lesser Heishan Island ||\u5c0f\u9ed1\u5c71\u5c9b||1.9||0.85||1.29||5.3||95.1\n|-\n|Miao Island (Temple Island)||\u5e99\u5c9b||2.65||1.1||1.43||6.7||98.3\n|-\n|Tuoji Island||\u7823\u77f6\u5c9b||4.75||3.9||7.05||17.68||198.9\n|-\n|Greater Qin Island||\u5927\u94a6\u5c9b||4.9||2||6.44||14.55||202.44\n|-\n|Lesser Qin Island||\u5c0f\u94a6\u5c9b||2||0.85||1.11||6.44||148.9\n|-\n|South Huangcheng Island||\u5357\u968d\u57ce\u5c9b||3.1||1.6||1.83||12.09||100.9\n|-\n|North Huangcheng Island||\u5317\u968d\u57ce\u5c9b||2.85||1.9||2.62||10.32||159.8\n|-\n|Yulin Island (Fish Scales Island)||\u9c7c\u9cde\u5c9b||0.17||0.1||0.01||0.38||19.5\n|-\n|South Tuozi Island||\u5357\u7823\u5b50\u5c9b||0.86||0.4||0.138||2.31||15.1\n|-\n|Niutuozi Island (Ox Rocky Island)||\u725b\u7823\u5b50\u5c9b||0.55||0.35||0.11||1.38||26.4\n|-\n|Yangtuozi Island (Goat Rocky Island)||\u7f8a\u7823\u5b50\u5c9b||0.55||0.35||0.11||1.38||26.4\n|-\n|Shaobing Island (Pancake Island)||\u70e7\u997c\u5c9b||0.14||0.1||0.02||0.38||19.6\n|-\n|Lijupa Island||\u7281\u728b\u628a\u5c9b||0.19||0.08||0.01||0.4||22.4\n|-\n|Xie Island (Scorpins Island)||\u874e\u5c9b||0.1||0.045||0.004||0.21||9.8\n|-\n|Houji Island||\u7334\u77f6\u5c9b||1.1||0.47||0.28||2.75||92.9\n|-\n|Lesser Houji Island||\u5c0f\u7334\u77f6\u5c9b||0.04||0.025||0.0009||0.22||23.3\n|-\n|Gaoshan Island||\u9ad8\u5c71\u5c9b||1.3||0.7||0.46||3.55||202.8\n|-\n|Lesser Gaoshan Island||\u5c0f\u9ad8\u5c71\u5c9b||0.035||0.025||0.0008||0.22||12.6\n|-\n|Greater Zhushan Island||\u5927\u7af9\u5c71\u5c9b||2.1||1.2||1.49||5.2||194.5\n|-\n|Lesser Zhushan Island||\u5c0f\u7af9\u5c71\u5c9b||0.8||0.4||0.24||2||97.2\n|-\n|Cheyou Island||\u8f66\u7531\u5c9b||0.64||0.1||0.05||1.25||73.5\n|-\n|Tuozi Island||\u7823\u5b50\u5c9b||0.42||0.15||0.05||1.06||60.3\n|-\n|Dongzuishi Island||\u4e1c\u5634\u77f3\u5c9b||0.05||0.04||0.002||0.15||7.2\n|-\n|Shanzuishi Island||\u5c71\u5634\u77f3\u5c9b||0.065||0.02||0.0013||0.17||16.7\n|-\n|Biegaishan Island (Turtle Shell Mount Island)||\u9cd6\u76d6\u5c71\u5c9b||0.2||0.11||0.02||0.57||42.8\n|-\n|Pojiao Island||\u5761\u7901\u5c9b||0.085||0.02||0.0017||0.15||12\n|-\n|Tanglang Island (Mantis Island)||\u87b3\u8782\u5c9b||0.97||0.25||0.15||2.01||54.7\n|-\n|Danglang Island (Wave Breaking Island)||\u6321\u6d6a\u5c9b||0.5||0.4||0.13||1.86||35.9\n|-\n|Maqiangshi Island||\u9a6c\u67aa\u77f3\u5c9b||0.1||0.016||0.0015||0.14||8.9||\n|}\n\n==Demographics==\nTen of the islands are occupied, and there are twenty-two uninhabited islands, some little more than sand spits. There is one large town, Tuoji Town (\u7823\u77f6\u9547, population 8,495) and seven smaller towns with forty villages, with a total population in the county of 52,000.\n\n==Economy==\nThe major occupation is [[aquaculture]], producing products such as [[sea cucumber]]s, [[abalone]], [[sea urchin]]s, [[bivalve]]s, [[kelp]], [[scallop]]s, [[prawn]]s and [[fish]].  [[Tourism]] is also important; many of the villages sport resort hotels.\n\n==Transportation==\nThe islands are regularly served by both a passenger and vehicle [[RORO|Roll On, Roll Off]] ferry from Penglai.  There is a small military airport on the largest island, Changdao Island.\n\n==Tourism==\nBoth Changdao National Forest Park and Changdao National Nature Reserve are located on the islands, which are on a cross-Bohai Sea flyway.\n\nTemple Island ({{zh|labels=no |t={{linktext|\u5edf\u5cf6}} |s={{linktext|\u5e99\u5c9b}} |p=Mi\u00e0od\u01ceo}}) got its name from the large number of temples that were built there. Xianying Palace is a temple that was built during the Northern Song Dynasty, starting in 1122. It was originally a [[Taoist]] temple to the sea goddess [[Matsu (goddess)|Matsu]], but became [[Buddhist]] later. At the present time the local government has restored the temple to its [[Ming Dynasty]] appearance, although many additions had been made during the [[Qing Dynasty|Qing]].\n\n{{citation needed span|Changdao Island was previously closed to non-Chinese nationals. Westerners found on the island were swiftly taken to the passenger ferry terminal and placed on the next ferry back to Penglai by the islands Police service. Islanders promptly reported all \"''outsiders''\" to the islands police service. Police explained the reasons for this was due to the high number of military installations on the Island. The Changdao Islands are now open to non-Chinese nationals, including westerners. This was agreed by the local and national governments as of 1 December 2008.|date=May 2018}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20071011030248/http://www.changdao.gov.cn/english/index.asp Official Changdao County website] \n* [http://www.changdao.net/ Changdao website from ''Yantai IDB'' development corporation] {{in lang|zh}}\n\n{{Yantai}}\n{{Shandong}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Nature reserves in China]]\n[[Category:County-level divisions of Shandong]]\n[[Category:Islands of Shandong]]\n[[Category:Island counties of China]]\n[[Category:Bohai Sea]]\n[[Category:Yantai]]\n", "name_user": "Seasonsinthesun", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eIslands", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Changdao_County"}
{"title_page": "GeeksPhone One", "text_new": "{{Infobox mobile phone\n| name            = GeeksPhone One\n| codename        = One\n| image           = [[File:GeeksPhone One.jpg|250px|GeeksPhone One]]\n| manufacturer    = [[GeeksPhone]]\n| type            = [[Smartphone]]\n| available       = 2010\n| connectivity    = [[GSM]] 850/900/1800/1900<br />[[Bluetooth]] 2.0<br />[[GPRS]]<br />[[HSDPA]]<br />[[Assisted GPS|AGPS]]<br />[[WiFi]] (802.11 b/g)<br />[[USB]]\n| media           = [[microSD]], [[Secure Digital card#SDHC|SDHC]] capable\n| operatingsystem = [[Android (operating system)|Android]] 1.6 Donut\n| input           = [[Touchscreen]]<br />5 hardware buttons<br />Volume slider<ref name=\"gp01\">{{cite web |url=http://wiki.geeksphone.com/en/index.php?title=Geeksphone_ONE |title=Geeksphone One |publisher=Geeksphone Wiki |accessdate=9 October 2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100518124814/http://wiki.geeksphone.com/en/index.php?title=Geeksphone_ONE |archive-date=18 May 2010 |df= }}</ref>\n| power           = 1110 mAh 3.7V Li-Po [[battery (electricity)|battery]]<ref name=\"gp01\" />\n| cpu             = 528 MHz ARM11 (ARM1136EJ-S) Jazelle series <ref name=\"gp01\" />\n| memory          = 256 MB mDDR<br/>512 MB NAND [[flash memory|flash]]<ref name=\"gp01\" />\n| dimensions      = 110 \u00d7 55 \u00d7 14 (mm)<ref name=\"gp01\" />\n| display         = 3.2&nbsp;in. WQVGA (240\u00d7400) TFT<ref name=\"aa01\">{{cite web |url=http://www.androidauthority.com/index.php/2009/11/30/review-geeksphone-one/ |title=Our review of the Geeks'Phone ONE |publisher=AndroidAuthority |accessdate=18 October 2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091205141045/http://www.androidauthority.com/index.php/2009/11/30/review-geeksphone-one/ |archive-date=5 December 2009 |df= }}</ref>\n| camera          = 3.1 Megapixels with autofocus<ref>{{Cite web|url= http://www.xataka.com/moviles/geeksphone-one-made-in-spain-opensource-y-con-android |title= Geeks\u2019Phone One: 'made in Spain', opensource y con Android |work= Xataka |date= 28 June 2009 |accessdate= 2009-09-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://and.roid.es/video-de-la-presentacion-del-geeksphone-one-en-el-androides-meetup.html/ |title=V\u00eddeo de la presentaci\u00f3n del GeeksPhone ONE en el and.roid.es MeetUP |work=and.roid.es |date=29 June 2009 |language=Spanish |accessdate=2009-09-04 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090901084631/http://and.roid.es/video-de-la-presentacion-del-geeksphone-one-en-el-androides-meetup.html |archive-date=2009-09-01 |df= }}</ref>\n}}\n\nThe '''GeeksPhone One''' is an [[Android (operating system)|Android]]-powered [[smartphone]] developed and marketed by [[GeeksPhone]].<ref name=\"engad09\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.engadget.com/2009/06/27/spanish-firm-geeksphone-launches-one-android-set/|title=Spanish firm GeeksPhone launches \"One\" Android set|publisher=[[Engadget]]|date=2009-06-27}}</ref> It is aimed at power users; GeeksPhone claims it to be the first Android phone which is not locked down but gives users full access to the operating system and even encourages modifying it. The device was originally priced at \u20ac300 in the EU, lowered to \u20ac160 in December 2010, and is currently out of stock.\n\n==Hardware==\n* [[GPS]] with [[DGPS]] ([[WAAS]]/[[EGNOS]])\n* 3-axis [[accelerometer]]\n* Retractile stylus<ref name=\"gp02\" />\n\nHardware specifications of the One were changed at various stages after its announcement: \n* The original prototype looked similar to the [[Samsung Omnia]]<ref name=\"ch01\">{{cite web|url=http://www.chip.de/news/GeeksPhone-Google-Handy-auf-Omnia-Basis_37083442.html|title=GeeksPhone: Google-Handy auf Omnia-Basis|publisher=Chip|language=German|accessdate=2010-01-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110928192944/http://www.chip.de/news/GeeksPhone-Google-Handy-auf-Omnia-Basis_37083442.html|archive-date=2011-09-28|url-status=dead}}</ref> and lacked a physical keyboard, the final design was adopted later.<ref name=\"gm01\">{{cite web|url=http://gizmovil.com/2009/10/geeksphone-one-nuevo-diseno-y-caracteristicas|title=Geeksphone ONE, nuevo dise\u00f1o y caracter\u00edsticas|language=Spanish|accessdate=2011-01-06}}</ref> \n* A DVB-T tuner, although initially announced, is not found in the final product.<ref name=\"ai01\">{{cite web|url=http://androinica.com/2009/06/29/geeksphone-one-is-an-android-phone-with-root-access/|title=Geeks\u2019Phone \"One\" is an Android phone with root access|publisher=Androinica|accessdate=2011-01-06}}</ref>\n* A second, front-facing camera for use in video calls<ref name=\"hdb01\">{{cite web |url=http://android.hdblog.it/2009/10/02/geeks-phone-one-caratteristiche-complete/ |title=Geeks Phone One - Caratteristiche complete |language=Italian |publisher=Forum Hdblog}}</ref> was also mentioned before the release and is clearly visible next to the earpiece in photos of prototypes,<ref name=\"au01\">{{cite web |url=http://www.androidup.com/geeksphone-one-al-via-il-pre-ordine-2663.html |title=Geeksphone One: Al via il pre ordine |language=Italian |publisher=AndroidUp |accessdate=27 October 2010}}</ref> although reportedly disabled in initial software releases. The final product lacks this second camera.\n* The first releases were shipped with 256 MB ROM; later models are equipped with 512 MB.<ref name=\"gp03\" />\n\n==Software==\nThe GeeksPhone One originally shipped with a customized build of Android 1.6 (Donut);<ref name=\"gp02\">{{cite web |url=http://www.geeksphone.com/es/moviles/especificaciones.php |title=Especificaciones GeeksPhone One |language=Spanish |publisher=[[GeeksPhone]] |accessdate=9 October 2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100923153020/http://www.geeksphone.com/es/moviles/especificaciones.php |archive-date=23 September 2010 |df= }}</ref> updates to later Android versions are available. The system image also includes closed-source Android components, as well as some commercial third-party applications.\n\n==Philosophy==\nThe GeeksPhone One is the first handset produced by GeeksPhone. The company claims it to be the first Android-powered handset which allows the user to modify operating system components without having to [[rooting (Android OS)|root]] the device first. New OS images can easily be installed on the device; the company operates a [[wiki]] and a forum for users to share knowledge. However, unlike similar efforts such as [[Openmoko]], GeeksPhone does not publish details on the phone's hardware beyond common technical specifications.\n\nAnother difference to Openmoko is that GeeksPhone aims to provide a stable device suitable for everyday use and capable of competing with other commercial devices on the market. The GeeksPhone One ships with an Android version which has undergone quality tests and passed Android Open Source Project (AOSP) Code Compliance certification, allowing it to include closed-source Android components and participate in Android Market.\n\nAs of July 2010, the GeeksPhone is not available through any of the big mobile operators. While GeeksPhone does not rule out cooperation with operators, CEO Javier Ag\u00fcera has stated that the \u201cfreedom-based\u201d business model would have priority over any such agreement.<ref name=ag01 />\n\n==Certified Community Release program==\nIn July 2010, GeeksPhone announced their Certified Community Release (CCR) program. CCRs are Android ports developed by the community and subsequently certified by GeeksPhone. Releases may be certified as \u201cstable\u201d or \u201cbeta\u201d. While full credit is given to the developer, GeeksPhone will give technical support to users of these builds and flash phones with a CCR if requested by the customer. Use of a CCR will not void the warranty of the phone.\n\nDevelopers can get technical support from GeeksPhone and major contributors may receive an additional free handset for development from GeeksPhone and, in some cases, sponsorships.<ref name=ag01>{{cite web |url=http://www.androidguys.com/2010/07/21/geeksphones-ccr-program-real-open-source-phone/ | title=Geeks'Phone's CCR Program: a Real Open-Source Phone |publisher=Android Guys |accessdate=18 October 2010}}</ref>\n\nGeeksPhone initially announced that phones would not yet ship with CCRs preinstalled; however, as of at least October 2010, phones have been shipped with a CCR based on Android 2.2 (Froyo).\n\n==Market availability and clones==\nGeeksPhone sells the One in Europe and Latin America. In Russia, computer discounter [[Vobis]] distributes the GeeksPhone One under the name [[Highscreen]] Zeus, apparently with a different software package than the original GeeksPhone One.<ref name=gp03>{{cite web |url=http://forum.geeksphone.com/index.php?topic=87.msg1522#msg1522 | title=\u00bfOtro \"hermano\" del One? |language=Spanish |publisher=GeeksPhone Forum |accessdate=27 October 2010}}</ref> In Taiwan and Hong Kong, it is marketed by [[FarEastOne]] under the name Commtiva Z1, with a Chinese keyboard.<ref name=\"mn01\">{{cite web |url=http://mobileandnotebook.com/reviews/smartphones/commtiva-z1-budget-android-smartphone-hands-on |title=Commtiva Z1 budget Android Smartphone hands on |publisher=mobile+notebook |accessdate=27 October 2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100323004406/http://mobileandnotebook.com/reviews/smartphones/commtiva-z1-budget-android-smartphone-hands-on |archive-date=23 March 2010 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"gp04\">{{cite web |url=http://forum.geeksphone.com/index.php?topic=67.msg1120#msg1120 | title=COMMTIVA Z1 o GeekPhone One r2 |language=Spanish |publisher=GeeksPhone Forum |accessdate=27 October 2010}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Acer Inc.|Acer]] [[Acer neoTouch P300|neoTouch P300]] appears to have identical hardware but runs [[Windows Mobile]].<ref name=\"gp05\">{{cite web |url=http://forum.geeksphone.com/index.php?topic=1029.0 | title=Windows Mobile 6.5 firmware |publisher=GeeksPhone Forum |accessdate=8 November 2010}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Google Nexus]]\n*[[Galaxy Nexus]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{[https://diario16.com/la-industria-del-entretenimiento-gana-fuerza-tras-la-crisis-del-covid-19/ plus]}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|http://www.geeksphone.com/en/}}\n\n{{Android smartphones}}\n\n[[Category:Android (operating system) devices]]\n[[Category:Mobile phones with an integrated hardware keyboard]]\n[[Category:Smartphones]]\n\n*''GeeksPhone One has [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/La_verdad_oculta#References peliculas online]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox mobile phone\n| name            = GeeksPhone One\n| codename        = One\n| image           = [[File:GeeksPhone One.jpg|250px|GeeksPhone One]]\n| manufacturer    = [[GeeksPhone]]\n| type            = [[Smartphone]]\n| available       = 2010\n| connectivity    = [[GSM]] 850/900/1800/1900<br />[[Bluetooth]] 2.0<br />[[GPRS]]<br />[[HSDPA]]<br />[[Assisted GPS|AGPS]]<br />[[WiFi]] (802.11 b/g)<br />[[USB]]\n| media           = [[microSD]], [[Secure Digital card#SDHC|SDHC]] capable\n| operatingsystem = [[Android (operating system)|Android]] 1.6 Donut\n| input           = [[Touchscreen]]<br />5 hardware buttons<br />Volume slider<ref name=\"gp01\">{{cite web |url=http://wiki.geeksphone.com/en/index.php?title=Geeksphone_ONE |title=Geeksphone One |publisher=Geeksphone Wiki |accessdate=9 October 2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100518124814/http://wiki.geeksphone.com/en/index.php?title=Geeksphone_ONE |archive-date=18 May 2010 |df= }}</ref>\n| power           = 1110 mAh 3.7V Li-Po [[battery (electricity)|battery]]<ref name=\"gp01\" />\n| cpu             = 528 MHz ARM11 (ARM1136EJ-S) Jazelle series <ref name=\"gp01\" />\n| memory          = 256 MB mDDR<br/>512 MB NAND [[flash memory|flash]]<ref name=\"gp01\" />\n| dimensions      = 110 \u00d7 55 \u00d7 14 (mm)<ref name=\"gp01\" />\n| display         = 3.2&nbsp;in. WQVGA (240\u00d7400) TFT<ref name=\"aa01\">{{cite web |url=http://www.androidauthority.com/index.php/2009/11/30/review-geeksphone-one/ |title=Our review of the Geeks'Phone ONE |publisher=AndroidAuthority |accessdate=18 October 2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091205141045/http://www.androidauthority.com/index.php/2009/11/30/review-geeksphone-one/ |archive-date=5 December 2009 |df= }}</ref>\n| camera          = 3.1 Megapixels with autofocus<ref>{{Cite web|url= http://www.xataka.com/moviles/geeksphone-one-made-in-spain-opensource-y-con-android |title= Geeks\u2019Phone One: 'made in Spain', opensource y con Android |work= Xataka |date= 28 June 2009 |accessdate= 2009-09-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://and.roid.es/video-de-la-presentacion-del-geeksphone-one-en-el-androides-meetup.html/ |title=V\u00eddeo de la presentaci\u00f3n del GeeksPhone ONE en el and.roid.es MeetUP |work=and.roid.es |date=29 June 2009 |language=Spanish |accessdate=2009-09-04 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090901084631/http://and.roid.es/video-de-la-presentacion-del-geeksphone-one-en-el-androides-meetup.html |archive-date=2009-09-01 |df= }}</ref>\n}}\n\nThe '''GeeksPhone One''' is an [[Android (operating system)|Android]]-powered [[smartphone]] developed and marketed by [[GeeksPhone]].<ref name=\"engad09\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.engadget.com/2009/06/27/spanish-firm-geeksphone-launches-one-android-set/|title=Spanish firm GeeksPhone launches \"One\" Android set|publisher=[[Engadget]]|date=2009-06-27}}</ref> It is aimed at power users; GeeksPhone claims it to be the first Android phone which is not locked down but gives users full access to the operating system and even encourages modifying it. The device was originally priced at \u20ac300 in the EU, lowered to \u20ac160 in December 2010, and is currently out of stock.\n\n==Hardware==\n* [[GPS]] with [[DGPS]] ([[WAAS]]/[[EGNOS]])\n* 3-axis [[accelerometer]]\n* Retractile stylus<ref name=\"gp02\" />\n\nHardware specifications of the One were changed at various stages after its announcement: \n* The original prototype looked similar to the [[Samsung Omnia]]<ref name=\"ch01\">{{cite web|url=http://www.chip.de/news/GeeksPhone-Google-Handy-auf-Omnia-Basis_37083442.html|title=GeeksPhone: Google-Handy auf Omnia-Basis|publisher=Chip|language=German|accessdate=2010-01-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110928192944/http://www.chip.de/news/GeeksPhone-Google-Handy-auf-Omnia-Basis_37083442.html|archive-date=2011-09-28|url-status=dead}}</ref> and lacked a physical keyboard, the final design was adopted later.<ref name=\"gm01\">{{cite web|url=http://gizmovil.com/2009/10/geeksphone-one-nuevo-diseno-y-caracteristicas|title=Geeksphone ONE, nuevo dise\u00f1o y caracter\u00edsticas|language=Spanish|accessdate=2011-01-06}}</ref> \n* A DVB-T tuner, although initially announced, is not found in the final product.<ref name=\"ai01\">{{cite web|url=http://androinica.com/2009/06/29/geeksphone-one-is-an-android-phone-with-root-access/|title=Geeks\u2019Phone \"One\" is an Android phone with root access|publisher=Androinica|accessdate=2011-01-06}}</ref>\n* A second, front-facing camera for use in video calls<ref name=\"hdb01\">{{cite web |url=http://android.hdblog.it/2009/10/02/geeks-phone-one-caratteristiche-complete/ |title=Geeks Phone One - Caratteristiche complete |language=Italian |publisher=Forum Hdblog}}</ref> was also mentioned before the release and is clearly visible next to the earpiece in photos of prototypes,<ref name=\"au01\">{{cite web |url=http://www.androidup.com/geeksphone-one-al-via-il-pre-ordine-2663.html |title=Geeksphone One: Al via il pre ordine |language=Italian |publisher=AndroidUp |accessdate=27 October 2010}}</ref> although reportedly disabled in initial software releases. The final product lacks this second camera.\n* The first releases were shipped with 256 MB ROM; later models are equipped with 512 MB.<ref name=\"gp03\" />\n\n==Software==\nThe GeeksPhone One originally shipped with a customized build of Android 1.6 (Donut);<ref name=\"gp02\">{{cite web |url=http://www.geeksphone.com/es/moviles/especificaciones.php |title=Especificaciones GeeksPhone One |language=Spanish |publisher=[[GeeksPhone]] |accessdate=9 October 2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100923153020/http://www.geeksphone.com/es/moviles/especificaciones.php |archive-date=23 September 2010 |df= }}</ref> updates to later Android versions are available. The system image also includes closed-source Android components, as well as some commercial third-party applications.\n\n==Philosophy==\nThe GeeksPhone One is the first handset produced by GeeksPhone. The company claims it to be the first Android-powered handset which allows the user to modify operating system components without having to [[rooting (Android OS)|root]] the device first. New OS images can easily be installed on the device; the company operates a [[wiki]] and a forum for users to share knowledge. However, unlike similar efforts such as [[Openmoko]], GeeksPhone does not publish details on the phone's hardware beyond common technical specifications.\n\nAnother difference to Openmoko is that GeeksPhone aims to provide a stable device suitable for everyday use and capable of competing with other commercial devices on the market. The GeeksPhone One ships with an Android version which has undergone quality tests and passed Android Open Source Project (AOSP) Code Compliance certification, allowing it to include closed-source Android components and participate in Android Market.\n\nAs of July 2010, the GeeksPhone is not available through any of the big mobile operators. While GeeksPhone does not rule out cooperation with operators, CEO Javier Ag\u00fcera has stated that the \u201cfreedom-based\u201d business model would have priority over any such agreement.<ref name=ag01 />\n\n==Certified Community Release program==\nIn July 2010, GeeksPhone announced their Certified Community Release (CCR) program. CCRs are Android ports developed by the community and subsequently certified by GeeksPhone. Releases may be certified as \u201cstable\u201d or \u201cbeta\u201d. While full credit is given to the developer, GeeksPhone will give technical support to users of these builds and flash phones with a CCR if requested by the customer. Use of a CCR will not void the warranty of the phone.\n\nDevelopers can get technical support from GeeksPhone and major contributors may receive an additional free handset for development from GeeksPhone and, in some cases, sponsorships.<ref name=ag01>{{cite web |url=http://www.androidguys.com/2010/07/21/geeksphones-ccr-program-real-open-source-phone/ | title=Geeks'Phone's CCR Program: a Real Open-Source Phone |publisher=Android Guys |accessdate=18 October 2010}}</ref>\n\nGeeksPhone initially announced that phones would not yet ship with CCRs preinstalled; however, as of at least October 2010, phones have been shipped with a CCR based on Android 2.2 (Froyo).\n\n==Market availability and clones==\nGeeksPhone sells the One in Europe and Latin America. In Russia, computer discounter [[Vobis]] distributes the GeeksPhone One under the name [[Highscreen]] Zeus, apparently with a different software package than the original GeeksPhone One.<ref name=gp03>{{cite web |url=http://forum.geeksphone.com/index.php?topic=87.msg1522#msg1522 | title=\u00bfOtro \"hermano\" del One? |language=Spanish |publisher=GeeksPhone Forum |accessdate=27 October 2010}}</ref> In Taiwan and Hong Kong, it is marketed by [[FarEastOne]] under the name Commtiva Z1, with a Chinese keyboard.<ref name=\"mn01\">{{cite web |url=http://mobileandnotebook.com/reviews/smartphones/commtiva-z1-budget-android-smartphone-hands-on |title=Commtiva Z1 budget Android Smartphone hands on |publisher=mobile+notebook |accessdate=27 October 2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100323004406/http://mobileandnotebook.com/reviews/smartphones/commtiva-z1-budget-android-smartphone-hands-on |archive-date=23 March 2010 |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"gp04\">{{cite web |url=http://forum.geeksphone.com/index.php?topic=67.msg1120#msg1120 | title=COMMTIVA Z1 o GeekPhone One r2 |language=Spanish |publisher=GeeksPhone Forum |accessdate=27 October 2010}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Acer Inc.|Acer]] [[Acer neoTouch P300|neoTouch P300]] appears to have identical hardware but runs [[Windows Mobile]].<ref name=\"gp05\">{{cite web |url=http://forum.geeksphone.com/index.php?topic=1029.0 | title=Windows Mobile 6.5 firmware |publisher=GeeksPhone Forum |accessdate=8 November 2010}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Google Nexus]]\n*[[Galaxy Nexus]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{[https://diario16.com/la-industria-del-entretenimiento-gana-fuerza-tras-la-crisis-del-covid-19/ plus]}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|http://www.geeksphone.com/en/}}\n\n{{Android smartphones}}\n\n[[Category:Android (operating system) devices]]\n[[Category:Mobile phones with an integrated hardware keyboard]]\n[[Category:Smartphones]]\n", "name_user": "HailieJadeSlim", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GeeksPhone_One"}
